org.micromanager.data

Interface RewritableStorage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Storage

    public interface RewritableStorage
extends Storage
    This interface is for Storage entities that allow the overwriting and deletion of Images and SummaryMetadata, as per RewritableDatastore.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

    • Method Detail

      • deleteImage

        void deleteImage(Coords coords)
          throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Delete an image from the Storage. Posts an ImageDeletedEvent to the event bus. Throws an IllegalArgumentException if the provided coordinates do not correspond to any image in the Storage.
        Parameters:
        coords - Coordinates of the image to remove.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the coords do not match any image.
